				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ Z=\frac{X_{tDCS}-{M}_{sham}}{S_{sham}} $$\end{document}Z=XtDCS−MshamSshamwhere XtDCS denotes the tDCS-related β value within each time window in real tDCS condition, Msham represents the mean of β values across all windows in the sham condition, and Ssham is the standard deviation of β values of all windows in the sham condition. The β values correspond to the regressors of the linear equation expressing the brain signal within the region-of-interest with respect of the mean signal and the differential effect induced by real tDCS and sham stimulations.
